<h3 class="date"><a href="/2008/oct/26/">&#x27a0;</a> October 26, 2008</h3>


<div class="row">
    <div class="span12">


    
    <div class="well" id="how-take-american-health-care-" >

        

        <h4><a class="taggedlink linklink" href="http://www.nytimes.com/2008/10/24/opinion/24beane.html?partner=rssuserland&amp;emc=rss&amp;pagewanted=all">How to Take American Health Care From Worst to First</a></h4>

        
            
        

        <p>Op-Ed piece encouraging taking &#8220;Moneyball&#8221; approach to healthcare.  Hands up anyone who ever thought they&#8217;d see the NYTimes run an article with the byline &#8220;By BILLY BEANE, NEWT GINGRICH and JOHN KERRY&#8221;.</p>

